{
  "texts": [
    "This involves evaluating the performance of cost-sensitive methods on multiple datasets, encompassing different medical institutions and patient populations.",
    "Furthermore, efforts should be made to address potential sources of dataset bias, covariate shift, and concept drift to enhance the models' generalizability to unseen data.",
    "• Considering interpretability: Interpretability is recognised as a critical consideration in developing cost-sensitive solutions.",
    "Guaranteeing interpretability within these models is paramount for cultivating transparency and understanding in clinical decision-making processes.",
    "Researchers are urged to prioritise the development of interpretable costsensitive techniques that strike a balance between model complexity and transparency."
  ]
}